<reference id="reference_B602C82274A1400CAD96F8F87548C457"> 
  <title>Managing Segments Prior to Upgrading</title> 
  <shortdesc><keyword>SiteCatalyst</keyword> 15 provides custom segments and
	 global access to shared 
	 <keyword>Discover</keyword> segments. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <refbody> 
	 <refsyn id="refsyn_8E21284AD4AC432E9C778E4691DA686C"> 
		<p>Before upgrading to 
		  <keyword>SiteCatalyst</keyword> 15, Adobe recommends auditing all
		  segments that are shared by 
		  <keyword>Discover</keyword> users, and selecting which segments should
		  appear in the 
		  <keyword>SiteCatalyst</keyword> segments list. Any segments that should
		  not be shared with all 
		  <keyword>SiteCatalyst</keyword> users should be moved to a non-shared
		  folder. Shared segments might need to be renamed since they are visible to all 
		  <keyword>SiteCatalyst</keyword> users. For example, you might prefix
		  global segments with CORP: or GLOBAL:, and personal segments with your name. 
		</p>
		<note>You cannot apply segments to a legacy dashboard.
		</note> 
